            <pb n="2" facs="#f0001" />
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">American Population.</hi>
                </head>
              <p>&#x2014; The celebrated<lb/>Prussian traveller and statesman, Humboldt,<lb/>has
          made the following calculations respect-<lb/>ing the population of America. He
          estimates<lb/>the total population at <choice>
            <sic>34,234,000</sic>
            <corr type="editorial">34,284,000</corr>
          </choice>, of which<lb/>22,177,000 are Catholics, 11,287,000 Protes-<lb/>tants, and
          820,000 Pagans; the English<lb/>language is spoken by 11,297,500, the<lb/>Spanish by
          10,174,000, the Indian languages<lb/>by <choice>
            <sic>7,800,800</sic>
            <corr type="editorial">7,800,000</corr>
          </choice>, the Portuguese by 3,740,000,<lb/>the French by <choice>
            <sic>1,358 000</sic>
            <corr type="editorial">1,058 000</corr>
          </choice>, the Dutch, &#x0026;c. by<lb/>214,500. The population of Spanish Ame-<lb/>rica
          is 15,985,000, of which 2,937,000 are<lb/>whites, 7,530,000 Indians, and
          5,518,000<lb/>mixed races and negroes: Portuguese<lb/>America contains 4,000,000 persons,
          of whom<lb/>920,000 are whites, 1,960,000 negroes, and<lb/>1,120,000 mixed races and
          Indians.</p>
            </div>
            <lb/>
        </body>
